                <head>No. 227.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Noyes</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-03-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 21, 1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President Grévy informally accepts invitation to Yorktown celebration, and says
                    that as France shared in the danger and cost of securing <pb facs="0529" n="405"
                        xml:id="pg_405"/> national independence to America, she gladly takes part in
                    rejoicing over the victory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>NOYES.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
